  "title": "Work-Energy theorem - changing angles of forces",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block moving to the right along a horizontal surface, pulled by a force labeled F.\" src=\"/images/e0b87e56bb983e257f7929591484a36a.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t equals t sub 0\"><math alttext=\"t equals t sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, a block is pulled to the right along a horizontal surface by a constant horizontal force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> as shown in the figure. Frictional forces between the block and the surface are negligible. At time <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"t equals t sub 1\"><math alttext=\"t equals t sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>t</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, the angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta\"><math alttext=\"theta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>θ</mi></math></span></span> between the force <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span> and the horizontal starts to increase without exceeding <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"90 degrees\"><math alttext=\"90 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi></math></span></span>, while the magnitude of the force remains constant. How does the kinetic energy of the object change as the angle increases?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy remains the same.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy increases.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy decreases.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The kinetic energy increases when <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta is less than 45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"theta is less than 45 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi></mstyle></math></span></span> and decreases when <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta is greater than 45 degrees\"><math alttext=\"theta is greater than 45 degrees\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>45</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">°</mi></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
